      "schema:description": "The FACT Network is a grassroots collaboration that is dedicated to improving the conservation and management of aquatic animals by facilitating data sharing amongst researchers using acoustic telemetry technology, provding a community for scientists, and building stakeholder partnerships. Conceived in 2007 as a means of tracking coastal fish and sea turtles in east-central Florida, the FACT Network rapidly expanded and currently spans from the southeastern United States into the Bahamas and U.S. Caribbean.",
